The paper deals with image captioning models and their attention mechanisms, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of explanation methods such as LRP and gradient backpropagation, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these methods for debiasing and improving the model, which is a topic of interest in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
